**Steps to Reproduce**:
I have the very simple `MyClass` in one project
```cs
public class MyClass
{
    private int _privateField;
}

```

And using [PrivateProxy](https://github.com/Cysharp/PrivateProxy) in another project in the same solution to automatically generate the proxy class. 
```cs
[GeneratePrivateProxy(typeof(MyClass))]
public partial struct MyClassProxy;
```
When using the extension method `AsPrivateProxy` will cause the `Error CS1061: 'MyClass' does not contain a definition for 'AsPrivateProxy' and no accessible extension method 'name' accepting a first argument of type 'MyClass' could be found (are you missing a using directive or an assembly reference?).`

I tried looking into PrivateProxy's source code to find a solution to use types from external dlls. I found out that because of #72369; the `INamedTypeSymbol.GetMembers()` call cannot access the private members of the class; therefore, the length of [Members after some execution](https://github.com/Cysharp/PrivateProxy/blob/2896a79bba4135e75ac3a3c834f537b99fb37eb6/src/PrivateProxy.Generator/PrivateProxyGenerator.cs#L87) should be 0 in this case (which is exactly 0 when debugging source generator, and if i comment out those lines, the whole thing compiles normally) . And [Line 94](https://github.com/Cysharp/PrivateProxy/blob/2896a79bba4135e75ac3a3c834f537b99fb37eb6/src/PrivateProxy.Generator/PrivateProxyGenerator.cs#L94) will cause the source generator to exit, so basically there should be no source generated files.

However, I could find the generated files both in Rider and VS
```cs
partial struct ClassLibraryMyClassProxy
{

    global::ClassLibrary.MyClass target;

    public ClassLibraryMyClassProxy(global::ClassLibrary.MyClass target)
    {
        this.target = target;
    }

    [UnsafeAccessor(UnsafeAccessorKind.Field, Name = "_privateField")]
    static extern ref int ___privateField__(global::ClassLibrary.MyClass target);

    public ref int _privateField => ref ___privateField__(this.target);
}

public static class MyClassPrivateProxyExtensions
{
    public static global::Test.ClassLibraryMyClassProxy AsPrivateProxy(this global::ClassLibrary.MyClass target)
    {
        return new global::Test.ClassLibraryMyClassProxy(target);
    }
}

}
```

Also, if i output the members.Length using source generator, it shows up 1 in the generated file
I think it's a some kind bug

